    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "yo i just finished replacing the brake pads on my 2018 camry but now when i test drive it i get this really high pitched squealing noise when i hit the brakes. not sure if its a worn sensor or if i messed up the caliper or something. what should i check first?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Squealing brakes, right after a pad change, is a common nuisance. You should check the caliper and the pads first, as they are the most likely culprits, though sometimes it's just a bit of grime or a loose piece of metal. A good, solid check is to inspect the caliper hardware for any signs of rubbing or binding. If the pads are new, make sure they are seated perfectly flush against the rotor; a slight misalignment can cause that high-pitched whine.",
      "source": "target",
