    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i checked the caliper and it looks like it's moving okay, but the sound is really sharp and constant right when the pressure is applied. it almost sounds like metal-on-metal but it's more of a piercing screech. do you think it could be a sensor issue or maybe a clip that didnt snap into place right?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A piercing screech, especially when the pressure is applied, sounds like something is grinding or rubbing aggressively. That's a classic sign that something isn't seating right, or maybe a piece of old, rusty shims is still clinging to the hardware. You need to look closely at those caliper clips, the little metal bits that hold the pads in place. Sometimes a clip doesn't snap home properly, and that little piece of metal is just vibrating against the rotor when you hit the brakes.",
      "source": "target",
